@startuml
title game-lib camera subsystem

left to right direction
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
hide empty members
hide circle

package "Public camera API" {
  class "createCamera(...)" as CreateCamera <<factory>>
  class CameraWrapper {
    +addBehavior(...)
    +removeBehavior(key)
    +addAction(...)
    +setPerspective(...)
    +getPerspective()
    +getState()
    +setViewport(viewport)
    +enableOrbitalControls()
    +disableOrbitalControls()
    +getRenderTexture()
  }
}

package "Runtime camera core" {
  class ZylemCamera {
    +targets: StageEntity[]
    +pipeline: CameraPipeline
    +viewport: Viewport
    +setTargets(targets)
    +setPerspective(perspective)
    +addBehavior(...)
    +removeBehavior(key)
    +addAction(...)
    +update(delta)
    +resize(width, height)
    +setRenderTarget(...)
  }

  class CameraPipeline {
    +setPerspective(perspective)
    +addBehavior(key, behavior)
    +removeBehavior(key)
    +addAction(action)
    +update(ctx, delta): CameraPose
  }

  interface CameraPerspective
  interface CameraBehavior
  interface CameraAction

  class CameraManager {
    +register(camera)
    +unregister(id)
    +setActive(ids)
    +setup(renderer)
    +update(delta)
    +render(scene)
  }

  class CameraOrbitController {
    +enable()
    +disable()
    +enterDebugMode()
    +exitDebugMode()
  }

  class RendererManager {
    +renderRTTCameras(...)
    +renderViewportCameras(...)
    +renderCamera(...)
  }

  class CameraContext <<type>>
  class CameraPose <<type>>
  class Viewport <<type>>
}

package "Perspective implementations" {
  class ThirdPersonPerspective
  class FirstPersonPerspective
  class Fixed2DPerspective
}

package "Stage/runtime collaborators" {
  class ZylemStage
  class ZylemScene
  class StageEntity
  class CameraDebugDelegate
}

package "External rendering types" {
  class "Three.js Camera" as ThreeCamera <<external>>
  class "WebGLRenderTarget" as RenderTarget <<external>>
}

CreateCamera --> CameraWrapper : returns
CreateCamera --> ZylemCamera : creates/configures

CameraWrapper *-- ZylemCamera : facade over

ZylemCamera *-- CameraPipeline
ZylemCamera o-- CameraOrbitController
ZylemCamera --> StageEntity : follow target(s)
ZylemCamera --> ThreeCamera : owns concrete camera
ZylemCamera --> Viewport : applies
ZylemCamera --> RenderTarget : optional RTT output

CameraPipeline --> CameraContext : consumes
CameraPipeline --> CameraPose : computes
CameraPipeline --> CameraPerspective : base pose from
CameraPipeline --> CameraBehavior : applies ordered modifiers
CameraPipeline --> CameraAction : applies transient deltas

ThirdPersonPerspective ..|> CameraPerspective
FirstPersonPerspective ..|> CameraPerspective
Fixed2DPerspective ..|> CameraPerspective

ThirdPersonPerspective --> StageEntity : follow / framing
FirstPersonPerspective --> StageEntity : eye/body anchor

CameraWrapper ..> CameraPerspective : set/get
CameraWrapper ..> CameraBehavior : add/remove
CameraWrapper ..> CameraAction : enqueue
CameraWrapper ..> Viewport : setViewport(...)

CameraManager o-- "0..*" ZylemCamera : manages
CameraManager --> RendererManager : renders through
CameraManager --> ZylemScene : renders active cameras into
ZylemStage --> CameraManager : owns stage camera set

CameraOrbitController ..> CameraDebugDelegate : debug orbit mode
RendererManager ..> ThreeCamera
RendererManager ..> RenderTarget

note right of CameraWrapper
Author-facing facade returned by `createCamera(...)`.

It exposes the ergonomic API used by game code
while delegating actual runtime work to `ZylemCamera`.
end note

note right of ZylemCamera
Live runtime camera object.

Responsibilities:
- own the concrete Three.js camera
- maintain target list
- run the camera pipeline each frame
- manage viewport and resize
- optionally render to texture
- bridge camera state into renderer usage
end note

note bottom of CameraPipeline
Per-frame pipeline order:

1. perspective computes a base pose
2. behaviors modify the desired pose
3. actions apply transient offsets/effects
4. damping/smoothing produces final committed pose
end note

note bottom of CameraManager
Stage-level multi-camera orchestration.

Typical render order:
- render-to-texture cameras first
- viewport/screen cameras second
end note

legend right
|= Part |= Role |
| `CameraWrapper` | public facade for app code |
| `ZylemCamera` | live runtime camera |
| `CameraPipeline` | deterministic pose computation pipeline |
| `CameraPerspective` | base framing strategy |
| `CameraBehavior` | reusable pose modifier |
| `CameraAction` | transient camera effect |
| `CameraManager` | multi-camera coordination |
| `RendererManager` | shared renderer backend |
endlegend

@enduml
